consequently /ˈkɒnsɪkwəntlɪ/

1. ADV Consequently means as a result. 结果 [正式] [ADV with cl] 

例： Grandfather had sustained a broken back while working in the mines. Consequently, he spent the rest of his life in a wheelchair. 爷爷在矿上做工时受了背伤，结果，他在轮椅上度过了他的余生。

